<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-12T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-12T15:00:00-05:00" n="484" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2199: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-12T15:00:00-05:00">April 12, 1934—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>48. Department’s telegram 31, April 11, 3 p.m. Leticia—American aviators.
                            Minister of Foreign Affairs takes Department’s message as a completely
                            friendly expression, saying our Government’s attitude gives the greatest
                            satisfaction and that he is reporting it to President, Cabinet, and
                            consultative board. He also has report from Freyre.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>